article.description: Emily Carter scored 18 points and Helena Sverrisdottir added 14 as TCU (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) won for the 10th time in its last 11 games with a 78-51 victory over Colorado State on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Lady Frogs take advantage of 22 turnovers, roll over Rams
article.linkText: Carter, No. 21 TCU easily handle Colorado St.
article.story:
FORT WORTH, Texas -- Emily Carter scored 18 points and Helena Sverrisdottir added 14 as TCU (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) won for the 10th time in its last 11 games with a 78-51 victory over Colorado State on Wednesday night.

TCU (15-4, 5-1 in Mountain West Conference) shot 46.9 percent from the field, including making half of its 12 3-pointers. The Lady Frogs led by as many as 33 points.

Chatilla van Grinsven led the Rams (11-8, 3-3) with 20 points. Colorado State struggled with 22 turnovers and hit just two of 19 3-pointers.

The Lady Frogs, which have won 17 in a row at home, led 37-23 at halftime. They quickly started the second half, hitting four 3-pointers to fuel a 23-7 spurt and put the game away.
